  "description": "LiteDRAM \u2014 a small, configurable DRAM controller core from the LiteX ecosystem. It is a GENERATED core: the LiteX/Migen generator (`litedram/gen.py`, a.k.a. litedram_gen) emits a self-contained `litedram_core.v` for a chosen DRAM module + PHY config (SDR/DDR/DDR2/DDR3/DDR4/LPDDR4), exposing a Native, AXI-MM, or Wishbone user interface. In the Vyges data plane it is the DRAM CONTROLLER behind the consolidated AXI link: the single AXI4 master from vyges-axi-dram-xbar (m_axi_dram) connects to litedram's AXI-MM user port. Primarily the soft-DDR controller for FPGA targets without a hardened DDR controller (e.g. Artix-7 standalone, Lattice); on ASIC the litedram controller pairs with a FOUNDRY hard DRAM PHY (litedram supplies the controller, not the ASIC LPDDR4 PHY). BSD-2-Clause (explicitly permits closed-source use). Mirror of enjoy-digital/litedram, pinned to release 2026.04.",
